WEBVTT

00:00.918 --> 00:02.501
- This is it.
We're here.

00:02.545 --> 00:04.420
This is krapopolis.

00:05.214 --> 00:06.839
I swear it's not as bad
as the name sounds.

00:06.924 --> 00:07.965
[creature shrieks]
- [screams]

00:08.092 --> 00:09.425
- Or that looked.
- I bet he deserved it.

00:09.510 --> 00:12.335
- Fisherman, your king returns.
- We have a king?

00:12.346 --> 00:14.304
- [laughs]
we're a democracy,

00:14.306 --> 00:16.423
So him not knowing me
means I'm crushing it.

00:16.434 --> 00:18.976
Oh, wow, and here's my family
to greet us.

00:19.061 --> 00:20.644
I guess you guys heard.
- Heard?

00:20.688 --> 00:23.313
- That I fought a kraken,
rescued a princess,

00:23.399 --> 00:25.941
And I'm returning
with a girlfriend.

00:25.985 --> 00:27.568
Am I rushing it?
- Nope.

00:27.695 --> 00:28.986
I'm his girlfriend.

00:29.030 --> 00:31.572
- Yeah,
it's the talk of the town.

00:31.615 --> 00:34.158
- I've got two grilled octopus
and two coconut waters.

00:34.243 --> 00:35.617
- That's us.
What do we owe you?

00:35.661 --> 00:37.828
- Three sandals.
- So you're only here for food?

00:37.913 --> 00:40.789
- In our defense, we got hungry
and forgot you were gone.

00:40.833 --> 00:42.124
Can you break a chicken?

00:42.168 --> 00:44.209
- Do I look like I carry
seven buckets of olives?

00:44.295 --> 00:46.295
- Hey, girlfriend,
welcome to krapopolis.

00:46.338 --> 00:47.421
- Oh!
- We need your sandals.

00:47.465 --> 00:50.174
- We are good for it.
We're royalty.

00:50.217 --> 00:53.343
<i> [dramatic lyre music]</i>

00:53.429 --> 01:00.476
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

01:06.734 --> 01:09.684
<i> [rhythmic grunting]</i>

01:09.695 --> 01:10.986
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

01:11.030 --> 01:13.238
<i> All: Whoo!</i>

01:15.367 --> 01:18.744
- The goddess deliria
demands this story continue.

01:18.788 --> 01:21.955
- Yes, mother--fifth time
you've interrupted to say that.

01:21.999 --> 01:23.290
- And I was tied to the rock,

01:23.334 --> 01:25.209
And the kraken
was going to eat me.

01:25.252 --> 01:29.046
But then, tyrannis arrived
and rescued me.

01:29.131 --> 01:32.257
- You rescued me.
- You rescued me.

01:34.011 --> 01:36.261
- You fought a kraken?
With what?

01:36.305 --> 01:38.806
- My fist--
punched it on the nose.

01:38.849 --> 01:39.932
I guess that's their weakness.

01:39.975 --> 01:41.350
- That's sharks.

01:41.435 --> 01:43.602
- Well,
turns out nobody likes it.

01:43.687 --> 01:46.105
- Herophile, tyrannis
tells me you're a sea nymph.

01:46.190 --> 01:47.314
Would we know your family?

01:47.399 --> 01:50.025
- Well, my father is poseidon.

01:50.111 --> 01:52.069
All: Ooh!
- Very impressive.

01:52.154 --> 01:54.988
- Oh, so when my son chooses
the daughter of a god,

01:55.074 --> 01:56.365
It's romantic, but--

01:56.450 --> 01:58.283
- But when your mother chooses,
it's gross.

01:58.327 --> 02:00.452
Yeah, you're getting it.
Come on.

02:00.496 --> 02:01.954
- You know what
I'm not getting?

02:02.039 --> 02:03.455
This kraken story.

02:03.541 --> 02:05.165
- Don't be jealous
of your brother, stupendous.

02:05.209 --> 02:06.416
- He can barely swim!

02:06.502 --> 02:08.210
How'd he untie her
in the water?

02:08.295 --> 02:10.129
- Krakens are bad with knots.

02:10.214 --> 02:12.422
- Once again, that's sharks.

02:12.466 --> 02:15.342
- I am bleeding to death.
That can wait.

02:15.386 --> 02:17.427
How is this
a feasible combination?

02:17.471 --> 02:20.389
- [mockingly]
that's tyrannis' girlfriend.

02:20.432 --> 02:22.975
- Oh, well,
I'm his half brother,

02:23.060 --> 02:24.643
Which I guess
makes us husband and wife

02:24.687 --> 02:27.104
If he gets murdered.
- You were bleeding to death?

02:27.189 --> 02:30.440
- Yeah, because guess
which animal still refuses

02:30.484 --> 02:33.318
To roll over for civilization?
- Wolves.

02:33.404 --> 02:34.695
- Wolves.
- Wolves!

02:34.864 --> 02:38.490
- What is with this rivalry
between humans and wolves?

02:38.576 --> 02:41.034
- They're the only animal
we will never be friends with.

02:41.120 --> 02:42.161
I'm just gonna
say it right now,

02:42.204 --> 02:43.245
They're man's worst enemy.

02:43.330 --> 02:44.872
- Brilliant,
that's gonna stick.

02:44.915 --> 02:46.456
- Mm-hmm.
- You realize this poor

02:46.458 --> 02:48.208
Young lady is sitting here
like a prop.

02:48.252 --> 02:50.085
Can we please give her
a bit of agency?

02:50.129 --> 02:51.879
Herophile,
I'd like you to decide

02:52.047 --> 02:53.630
When you're marrying my son.

02:53.716 --> 02:55.007
- Mom, we just met!

02:55.092 --> 02:57.426
- Her father is poseidon.

02:57.511 --> 02:59.845
- He's gonna propose
to you before sundown.

02:59.930 --> 03:02.055
[munches]
[muffled] here's why--

03:02.099 --> 03:05.267
You're the hottest woman
he'll ever have a shot at.

03:05.269 --> 03:07.811
- This family is
the wolves of people.

03:07.897 --> 03:09.771
<i> [dramatic music]</i>

03:09.815 --> 03:12.274
I guess the legend of our
relationship is spreading now.

03:12.401 --> 03:15.319
- I can't believe the king's
not going to die a virgin!

03:15.404 --> 03:17.279
- Inappropriate!
But hopefully, true.

03:17.406 --> 03:18.447
And there's where people eat,

03:18.532 --> 03:19.531
And there's where they poo.

03:19.700 --> 03:22.242
- Those places are really
close together.

03:22.328 --> 03:25.662
- That's exactly what I said.
You're good at this.

03:25.664 --> 03:27.206
Look, we're on a vase.

03:27.291 --> 03:29.750
- Being in a celebrated
relationship feels

03:29.793 --> 03:31.668
Extra romantic, doesn't it?

03:31.712 --> 03:34.379
- I guess that's why we should
put extra effort into knowing

03:34.465 --> 03:36.173
Where we're at,
keeping it real.

03:36.217 --> 03:37.799
- That's smart.
I agree.

03:37.927 --> 03:39.218
- Your divine royalnesses,

03:39.261 --> 03:42.638
I made a sculpture
of you two meeting.

03:42.765 --> 03:44.514
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

03:44.600 --> 03:46.934
- Holy balls.

03:47.019 --> 03:48.227
Marry me.
- Yes!

03:48.270 --> 03:49.561
Mmm.

03:49.647 --> 03:52.731
[cheers and applause]
- they're getting married--

03:52.816 --> 03:54.942
Mostly because of my work!

03:55.027 --> 03:58.278
- Wolves,
they're smart, yet savage--

03:58.405 --> 04:01.365
Organized, yet impulsive.
- Not unlike man.

04:01.450 --> 04:04.701
- Shlub, if you start with that
"man is just an animal" crap,

04:04.787 --> 04:06.119
I will pin you to the floor

04:06.247 --> 04:08.247
And dominate you
with a non-sexual hump.

04:08.332 --> 04:11.458
- That's why you're the cyclops
for this mission, sis.

04:11.502 --> 04:15.128
This new technology will
allow you to walk among wolves,

04:15.214 --> 04:16.797
Perceived as one of their own.

04:16.924 --> 04:18.215
- Is that a tank of wolf pee?

04:18.217 --> 04:20.050
- Is that a problem?
- You callin' me scared?

04:20.094 --> 04:22.302
I will non-sexually hump you.

04:22.346 --> 04:24.304
- Kids, kids,
there's no need to fight.

04:24.390 --> 04:26.807
We'll all get our chance
in the [bleep] tank.

04:26.850 --> 04:28.350
- Then let's begin!

04:28.894 --> 04:29.810
<i> [tense music]</i>

04:29.895 --> 04:30.978
[both grunt]

04:31.063 --> 04:35.816
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

04:35.901 --> 04:36.900
- Aah!

04:36.944 --> 04:39.861
<i> [dramatic music]</i>

04:39.905 --> 04:44.866
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

04:44.910 --> 04:46.618
[growls]

04:46.662 --> 04:50.998
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

04:52.293 --> 04:53.625
Ah!

04:53.669 --> 04:57.004
[grunting]

04:57.089 --> 05:00.215
<i> [tense music]</i>

05:00.301 --> 05:01.591
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

05:01.635 --> 05:03.802
- [sniffing]

05:03.846 --> 05:05.804
[growls]

05:05.889 --> 05:09.182
[both growling]

05:17.776 --> 05:19.568
[whimpers]

05:19.611 --> 05:21.653
- Now that we're friends,
what do you say

05:21.739 --> 05:22.946
We visit your leader?

05:23.032 --> 05:25.657
- [vocalizes]

05:25.701 --> 05:28.076
- My mother will be so happy
we're getting married,

05:28.162 --> 05:29.619
Which I don't even see
as a downside now.

05:29.705 --> 05:31.913
- And I'm so happy
that I'm not even turned off

05:32.041 --> 05:33.415
By how much you mention her.

05:33.459 --> 05:35.292
- I guess I do fixate too much
on proving her wrong.

05:35.377 --> 05:36.960
She represents the old world,

05:37.046 --> 05:39.087
And I never saw a role
for myself in it.

05:39.173 --> 05:41.089
Then I punched a kraken.
I'm a kraken puncher.

05:41.133 --> 05:42.924
- Yeah, you are.

05:42.968 --> 05:44.968
Is that a--
is that a kraken?

05:45.763 --> 05:48.213
- Oh, god, oh, dear god,
do you think it's the same one?

05:48.265 --> 05:49.973
Do I just punch it again?
- I don't know!

05:50.017 --> 05:51.183
- Well, get behind me, I guess.

05:51.268 --> 05:52.851
Or should we run?
- I don't know!

05:52.936 --> 05:54.186
- If we run,
will you still love me?

05:54.229 --> 05:55.854
- I think so.
- Oh, thank god. Run!

05:55.898 --> 05:56.980
[gasps]
- oh!

05:57.066 --> 05:58.065
- You run, and you're dead.

05:58.150 --> 05:59.316
- Oh, damn it.

05:59.360 --> 06:01.860
- Where's your mother?
She stiffed me.

06:01.945 --> 06:04.196
- See, I'm not the only one
who brings her up--wait, what?

06:04.281 --> 06:05.864
- Excuse me,
what are you saying?

06:05.949 --> 06:09.368
- His mother owes me 20 cows
for the fake kraken fight!

06:09.411 --> 06:11.078
- You're not a real kraken?

06:11.163 --> 06:14.456
- Real kraken, jagoff,
fake fight.

06:15.376 --> 06:18.418
[all grunting]

06:19.671 --> 06:23.048
<i> [mystical music]</i>

06:23.092 --> 06:24.091
- Whoa.
- Ah.

06:24.134 --> 06:25.384
[exclamations]

06:25.469 --> 06:26.551
- [roars]

06:26.637 --> 06:27.636
- Oh, a kraken!

06:27.679 --> 06:28.804
- Oh, no!
- [grunts]

06:28.889 --> 06:30.680
- Ah!
[water splashes]

06:30.766 --> 06:32.349
- [grunts]
- aah!

06:32.434 --> 06:35.727
- [grunts]
- oh! Owie, owie, owie!

06:35.771 --> 06:37.604
- [panting]

06:37.689 --> 06:39.523
[whimpers]

06:39.608 --> 06:40.565
[grunts weakly]

06:40.651 --> 06:42.609
- [groaning]

06:42.694 --> 06:44.736
I am slain!

06:44.780 --> 06:46.113
Ugh.

06:47.699 --> 06:51.118
You tell that bitch I'm hungry,
and I'm not going away!

06:51.161 --> 06:52.744
Sorry about the language,
sweetie.

06:52.830 --> 06:54.413
I respect poseidon a lot.

06:54.415 --> 06:56.915
Your dad's what krakens call
a kraken's god.

06:56.959 --> 06:58.375
Oh, and congratulations.

06:58.460 --> 07:00.919
[chuckling]
I heard you guys got engaged.

07:01.004 --> 07:03.255
- Thank you...
- Thank you...

07:03.298 --> 07:07.008
- ♪ and deliria's son
fought a kraken and won ♪

07:07.094 --> 07:09.177
♪ because he's deliria's son ♪

07:09.263 --> 07:11.930
- Loving it.
- ♪ and poseidon's daughter ♪

07:12.015 --> 07:13.432
♪ called out from the water-- ♪

07:13.475 --> 07:15.350
- Okay, but poseidon
can have his own song.

07:15.477 --> 07:17.477
What if that's where you put
a catchy hook, like--

07:17.563 --> 07:20.689
♪ this is the wedding
of deliria's son ♪

07:20.732 --> 07:25.152
♪ deliria, deliria ♪

07:25.195 --> 07:27.654
- I love that idea.
I'll come up with some lyrics.

07:27.739 --> 07:29.156
- I just gave you the lyrics.

07:29.199 --> 07:31.158
- Manipulator!
- [groans]

07:31.201 --> 07:32.409
Who told?
The kraken?

07:32.453 --> 07:34.286
- What happened to the crew?
Did they drown?

07:34.371 --> 07:36.121
- I turned them into fish
when they hit the water,

07:36.165 --> 07:37.164
Brought them home,

07:37.291 --> 07:38.248
And set them up
with wives of their own.

07:38.417 --> 07:41.334
Unlike you,
they won't be complaining.

07:41.420 --> 07:42.919
- Do you mind?
- No problem!

07:43.005 --> 07:46.631
[lute plays]

07:46.717 --> 07:47.924
- I mean, leave the room!

07:48.010 --> 07:49.926
- Don't talk to my bard
like a slave.

07:50.012 --> 07:51.553
You leave, and you die.
- No problem!

07:51.638 --> 07:54.014
- I thought I was in love!
- You are!

07:54.099 --> 07:56.349
And she's quite taken with you,
oddly enough.

07:56.435 --> 07:58.435
But if the blabbermouth kraken
changed that,

07:58.520 --> 08:00.061
We'll just sweeten
the deal for her.

08:00.189 --> 08:01.855
- I don't want her
to get a deal.

08:01.940 --> 08:03.106
I told you my whole life

08:03.192 --> 08:04.983
I don't want to be
provided with a woman.

08:05.110 --> 08:07.319
- Yes, yes,
you want to earn a woman

08:07.446 --> 08:09.362
By giving her more things
than someone better looking.

08:09.406 --> 08:12.115
It's quite modern, son.
But we've given it a go.

08:12.159 --> 08:13.658
I can't make another child.

08:13.744 --> 08:15.118
You were too much work.

08:15.162 --> 08:17.704
You owe me a grandson
worthy of overthrowing you.

08:17.748 --> 08:21.124
- Well, now I can die the
world's most satisfied virgin

08:21.168 --> 08:23.668
Since I'll finally be
depriving you of something.

08:23.754 --> 08:24.753
- Maybe I should go.

08:24.838 --> 08:25.921
Both: No!
- I'm going.

08:26.006 --> 08:27.923
I have a princess to return.

08:27.966 --> 08:30.091
- So sorry I tried to help you.

08:31.261 --> 08:33.178
- If there were anyone
in this entire world

08:33.263 --> 08:34.513
That wanted your help, mother,

08:34.598 --> 08:37.432
You'd be ruining their life
instead of mine!

08:38.602 --> 08:42.437
- ♪ this is the wedding
of deliria's-- ♪

08:42.523 --> 08:43.313
Spiders!

08:43.398 --> 08:44.523
Oh, god, why?

08:44.608 --> 08:46.900
Are they poisonous?
They're not biting.

08:46.985 --> 08:49.528
They're everywhere!
Can I just ask why?

08:49.613 --> 08:52.322
I'll take that as a no!
Whatever I did, I'm sorry!

08:52.407 --> 08:55.158
So many spiders!
Am I allowed to kill them?

08:55.202 --> 08:57.577
I'm killing a lot of them
just by flailing.

08:57.663 --> 09:00.163
If that's some kind of test,
I can try to stand still.

09:00.165 --> 09:01.915
I'll do anything!
I'm so sorry

09:01.959 --> 09:03.208
For whatever I did
to offend you!

09:03.293 --> 09:05.752
I have to get out
of these clothes!

09:05.796 --> 09:08.338
You know, your son does
seem pretty mad at you.

09:11.385 --> 09:14.261
<i> [somber music]</i>

09:14.346 --> 09:16.137
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

09:16.181 --> 09:18.348
- I'm not doing any actual
navigating, by the way.

09:18.392 --> 09:20.100
I'm just moving
this thing around.

09:20.227 --> 09:21.184
Where do you live again?

09:21.270 --> 09:23.186
- The ocean.
We're here.

09:23.230 --> 09:25.272
- Sorry I'm not
a real kraken puncher.

09:25.357 --> 09:27.065
- I didn't like you for that.

09:27.109 --> 09:28.775
I liked that you wanted

09:28.860 --> 09:31.111
To be free from the gods.

09:31.196 --> 09:33.446
- And here I am dumping you
back with poseidon.

09:33.532 --> 09:35.323
- And then going back
to deliria.

09:35.367 --> 09:37.325
- Gods, they think
they're so high and mighty,

09:37.411 --> 09:39.119
But they're--
well, they're high and mighty,

09:39.162 --> 09:40.412
But they're the ones
that need us.

09:40.497 --> 09:42.455
It would serve them right
if you and I just--

09:42.541 --> 09:44.040
- Disappeared?
I know a place

09:44.084 --> 09:46.585
We could live free.
It's called "the swamp."

09:46.628 --> 09:47.586
The gods never go there.

09:47.713 --> 09:49.796
- Unless "the swamp"
is a special name

09:49.881 --> 09:51.131
For a place that isn't a swamp,

09:51.174 --> 09:52.465
I don't think
anyone goes there.

09:52.509 --> 09:55.135
- Oh, it's a swamp,
but it's a swamp we control.

09:55.262 --> 09:56.803
We could have a kingdom there

09:56.805 --> 09:58.179
And<i> kids.</i>

09:58.223 --> 09:59.931
- [giggles]
we could try,

10:00.017 --> 10:01.349
Which I hear is the best part.

10:01.435 --> 10:02.934
And then the kids are--
[blows raspberry]

10:03.020 --> 10:04.311
- Let's do it, tyrannis.

10:04.354 --> 10:05.604
- Let's try it.
Let's swamp it.

10:05.689 --> 10:08.148
- You really mean it?
- I really mean let's try.

10:08.233 --> 10:10.025
<i> [romantic music]</i>

10:10.068 --> 10:12.193
- [barks]
- hey, everybody.

10:12.237 --> 10:15.447
Two wolves approachin'.
I'll be living with you guys,

10:15.532 --> 10:18.658
Learning your secrets--
not that they're secrets to me.

10:18.785 --> 10:19.784
I'm a wolf.

10:19.870 --> 10:21.620
<i> [tense music]</i>

10:21.747 --> 10:23.788
- [growling]

10:23.832 --> 10:24.956
[sniffs]

10:25.000 --> 10:25.957
- [sniffs]

10:26.001 --> 10:27.709
- [snarls]

10:27.753 --> 10:30.587
- Is that your boss?
What'd he say, something good?

10:30.672 --> 10:31.379
[all snarling]

10:31.465 --> 10:32.339
- [grunts]

10:32.466 --> 10:33.965
Well, that'll
keep the rain out.

10:34.051 --> 10:35.592
I guess the floor got kind of--

10:35.636 --> 10:37.135
- Swamped?
- Exactly.

10:37.179 --> 10:38.720
Hungry?
I'm going to check

10:38.764 --> 10:40.889
On the frog trap.

10:40.974 --> 10:42.849
Ew.
[groaning]

10:42.934 --> 10:44.309
Eww.

10:45.896 --> 10:48.772
I may not know
how to trap frogs.

10:48.815 --> 10:50.065
- But we're free.

10:50.150 --> 10:52.942
- Right, and now
we have to stay free forever,

10:52.986 --> 10:54.486
Or I'll be killed.

10:54.529 --> 10:55.236
[water splashes]

10:55.280 --> 10:56.488
Oh, boy, get behind me.

10:56.531 --> 10:58.156
I need a weapon.
I need a stick!

10:58.241 --> 11:00.784
Great, now I'm
a master frog catcher.

11:00.869 --> 11:03.286
<i> [suspenseful music]</i>

11:03.330 --> 11:04.120
- Carrots?

11:04.164 --> 11:05.580
- Herophile.

11:05.666 --> 11:06.790
Oh, who are you?

11:06.833 --> 11:08.541
- Her boyfriend.
- I see.

11:08.585 --> 11:10.585
I'm heartbroken,
but I'm not the jealous type.

11:10.629 --> 11:13.213
- You don't have to be.
You have a horse penis.

11:13.340 --> 11:15.048
I'm jealous.
What's the story here?

11:15.133 --> 11:17.884
- Carrots was my first love.
He left me.

11:17.969 --> 11:19.219
- I had to flee
from your father.

11:19.262 --> 11:21.221
I ended up on a tiny island,

11:21.348 --> 11:23.515
Imprisoned by irresistible
centaur women--

11:23.600 --> 11:26.101
Women with the backs
and fronts of horses.

11:26.186 --> 11:28.311
After a year, I realized,
wait, these are just horses.

11:28.397 --> 11:29.854
So I left.
And I remembered

11:29.898 --> 11:31.439
How you used to talk
about the swamp.

11:31.525 --> 11:33.942
- Can we go back to the year
you spent banging horses?

11:34.027 --> 11:35.193
- I could've lied
about that part.

11:35.237 --> 11:36.319
- That's definitely true.

11:36.405 --> 11:37.987
- I didn't come here
to get you back.

11:38.073 --> 11:39.155
- I'll believe it
when I see it.

11:39.199 --> 11:40.323
- I'm just hiding
from your dad.

11:40.367 --> 11:42.158
- Us too.
- Yeah, us too,

11:42.202 --> 11:43.743
The couple moving
into her swamp.

11:43.829 --> 11:45.453
Good luck out there, carrots.

11:46.832 --> 11:48.665
- Tyrannis, he'll die.

11:48.750 --> 11:50.583
- I said "good luck."

11:50.669 --> 11:51.918
[groans]

11:51.962 --> 11:53.837
Carrots, please do me the honor

11:53.880 --> 11:56.715
Of living in a swamp with me
and your ex-girlfriend.

11:56.800 --> 11:57.757
- I appreciate that.

11:57.843 --> 11:58.925
- I'm saying this right now.

11:59.094 --> 12:00.927
You're both dicks
if you fall back in love,

12:01.012 --> 12:03.012
And I don't care
if my ugly possessiveness

12:03.140 --> 12:04.472
Makes it feel romantic.

12:04.474 --> 12:06.182
It won't be.
It'll be a dick move

12:06.226 --> 12:07.434
That got called ahead of time.

12:07.477 --> 12:09.894
- Perfectly reasonable.
- No, that makes sense.

12:09.980 --> 12:11.438
- [shivers]

12:15.277 --> 12:16.568
[shivers]

12:17.362 --> 12:18.445
[twig snaps]

12:19.531 --> 12:21.322
- [snarling]

12:21.408 --> 12:23.491
- Step back.
I'm not wounded.

12:23.577 --> 12:27.036
I'm just in this position
because it's badass.

12:27.080 --> 12:29.038
- [vocalizes]

12:29.082 --> 12:31.166
- I said "get back!"
[grunts]

12:32.043 --> 12:35.712
<i> [hopeful music]</i>

12:35.797 --> 12:37.046
- [whimpers]

12:37.132 --> 12:38.798
- You makin' fun of me?

12:38.884 --> 12:43.636
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

12:43.722 --> 12:47.348
You bring one more stick to me
and see what happens.

12:47.392 --> 12:49.309
Thanks for bringing
all those sticks.

12:49.394 --> 12:51.936
- [vocalizing]

12:52.022 --> 12:54.647
- I assume this is,
like, a truce.

12:54.691 --> 12:57.942
So I'm gonna lay down
and either heal or die,

12:58.028 --> 12:59.611
And I'll kill you
in the morning.

12:59.696 --> 13:02.655
- [vocalizing]

13:07.662 --> 13:09.704
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

13:09.790 --> 13:13.291
[deer whimper and bray]

13:13.919 --> 13:15.168
- Hunger--uh--
- hungry!

13:15.253 --> 13:16.878
Hungry hunger!
- Eating.

13:16.963 --> 13:18.213
Food?
- Yes!

13:18.256 --> 13:19.547
- Come on,
this game was supposed

13:19.591 --> 13:21.925
To take our minds
off starvation.

13:21.968 --> 13:25.136
- [crying]
- don't cry, herophile.

13:25.222 --> 13:27.213
We still have one more round.
We can come back.

13:27.224 --> 13:28.848
- I prayed to my father.

13:28.934 --> 13:30.850
Both: What?
- Okay, you can cry now.

13:30.894 --> 13:32.310
Cry hard.
You just killed us!

13:32.354 --> 13:34.312
- I'm sorry.
I didn't know

13:34.356 --> 13:36.314
I'd be on the hook
for everyone's misery.

13:36.399 --> 13:37.732
- Now you're on the hook
for our deaths.

13:37.818 --> 13:40.276
Okay, this is good though.
If we're all being honest,

13:40.320 --> 13:42.862
I hate the swamp,
and I want my mommy.

13:42.948 --> 13:44.531
[grunts]
- what are you doing?

13:44.616 --> 13:46.199
- My mom gave me
an emergency ritual--

13:46.284 --> 13:49.077
Some moss,
a good-looking rock, mud.

13:49.162 --> 13:51.204
Gonna just--this looks
like my mom, I think, right?

13:51.331 --> 13:53.039
- You're spending a lot
of time on the breasts.

13:53.124 --> 13:54.958
- You don't get to judge
family dynamics!

13:55.043 --> 13:56.793
Goddess deliria,
mother of the ungrateful,

13:56.837 --> 13:57.794
Goddess deliria,

13:57.879 --> 13:58.837
Mother of the ungrateful--

13:58.922 --> 13:59.879
- My father is coming.
- Shh!

13:59.998 --> 14:00.922
Goddess deliria,

14:01.007 --> 14:01.965
Mother of the ungrateful!

14:02.050 --> 14:04.425
- This is the goddess deliria!

14:04.511 --> 14:05.468
- Yes, yes!

14:05.637 --> 14:07.303
Mom, I'm sorry,
and I need you just to--

14:07.347 --> 14:09.430
- If you'd like
to leave a sacrifice,

14:09.474 --> 14:12.058
You can do so
after this message.

14:12.102 --> 14:14.644
If not, lose this ritual.

14:14.729 --> 14:15.645
- Frog, frog!

14:15.730 --> 14:16.771
Give me the frog!

14:16.857 --> 14:19.649
<i> [dramatic music]</i>

14:19.734 --> 14:21.025
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

14:21.069 --> 14:22.360
- Dolphin skis!
Both: Ew.

14:22.445 --> 14:24.946
- I hope you're happy.
This brackish water

14:25.031 --> 14:26.030
Is killing these guys.

14:26.074 --> 14:27.282
[dolphins vocalizing]

14:27.325 --> 14:29.534
Yeah, you're fine now,
but trust me!

14:29.578 --> 14:30.493
- I'm sorry, dad.
I--

14:30.662 --> 14:31.911
- I don't wanna hear it.
Daddy's here.

14:31.997 --> 14:33.788
This ends now.
You're getting married.

14:33.832 --> 14:35.081
Where are these jackasses?

14:35.166 --> 14:37.125
Get over here!

14:37.210 --> 14:39.002
You, horse ass,
what's your name?

14:39.045 --> 14:40.044
Gravy?
- Carrots.

14:40.130 --> 14:41.296
- I don't wanna hear it!

14:41.381 --> 14:43.464
And you, you're deliria's kid,
titmouse?

14:43.466 --> 14:45.884
- Yes.
- That's your name, titmouse?

14:45.969 --> 14:47.176
- No.
- Tell me your name!

14:47.262 --> 14:49.128
- Tyrannis.
- I don't wanna hear it!

14:49.180 --> 14:50.346
Here's how it's gonna go down.

14:50.390 --> 14:52.223
I don't care who marries her
at this point.

14:52.267 --> 14:54.183
One of you is.
The other one is dying.

14:54.227 --> 14:56.352
- Dad, no!
Don't make me choose.

14:56.438 --> 14:58.980
- I'm not.
You'd choose wrong.

14:59.065 --> 15:01.399
At dawn, the two of you
fight to the death

15:01.443 --> 15:03.610
For my amusement,
but more importantly,

15:03.737 --> 15:04.944
To uphold--

15:05.030 --> 15:06.821
No, no--for my amusement.

15:06.907 --> 15:08.197
These dolphins are dying!

15:08.283 --> 15:10.158
[dolphins vocalize]
yes, you are!

15:10.201 --> 15:12.535
Dying dolphin skis!

15:16.917 --> 15:18.374
- Sorry.
- Sorry.

15:18.501 --> 15:19.500
- I'm sorry, guys.

15:19.544 --> 15:21.252
- You're sorry?
- Should I not be?

15:21.338 --> 15:22.795
- I was more expressing like,

15:22.839 --> 15:24.797
Sorry doesn't begin
to cover it.

15:24.841 --> 15:26.090
- We're blaming me for this?

15:26.134 --> 15:28.676
- Well, you did bring me
to a secret swamp

15:28.803 --> 15:31.054
Where your ex-boyfriend lives,
and then brought your father

15:31.097 --> 15:33.806
To the secret swamp, so I'm not
gonna blame the crocodiles.

15:33.934 --> 15:35.850
- We were going to die.

15:35.894 --> 15:36.976
- You guys were.

15:37.062 --> 15:39.479
I eat grass.
I was surviving.

15:39.564 --> 15:41.230
Now you're surviving,
and one of us isn't.

15:41.316 --> 15:43.483
- And to be clear,
whichever of us does survive,

15:43.526 --> 15:44.984
Will always agree
with the dead one

15:45.028 --> 15:46.277
That you could've
handled this better.

15:46.363 --> 15:48.279
- Gee, I can't wait
to be forced to marry

15:48.365 --> 15:50.949
The most lethal of two men
that despise me.

15:50.984 --> 15:52.450
[both chuckle]
is that funny?

15:52.535 --> 15:54.827
- No, but it is funny
to pick this moment

15:54.913 --> 15:55.954
To expect our sympathy.

15:56.039 --> 15:57.664
- Yeah, cry us a river.

15:57.749 --> 15:59.123
- Cry us a swamp.

15:59.167 --> 16:00.959
Look, don't worry.
Carrots and I have a plan.

16:01.044 --> 16:02.543
- Poseidon might
not even show up.

16:02.629 --> 16:04.545
- Are you serious?
- Sometimes he makes people

16:04.631 --> 16:06.506
Stand around all day,
and that's the lesson.

16:06.549 --> 16:09.384
- I love that lesson!
- Yup, let's get out of here.

16:09.386 --> 16:11.719
- Time to fight to the death!

16:11.805 --> 16:13.012
- Damn it.

16:13.098 --> 16:14.138
- You should stay in my room

16:14.224 --> 16:16.182
Until my family
can get used to you.

16:16.267 --> 16:18.267
But I walk around a lot.
You like walking around?

16:18.353 --> 16:20.436
And after a while,
maybe our species

16:20.522 --> 16:21.729
Can form some kind of...

16:21.773 --> 16:23.731
- Attention, wolves!

16:23.775 --> 16:25.942
Withdraw or die!

16:26.027 --> 16:29.153
- Friendship.
- You're no match for humanity!

16:29.239 --> 16:32.323
You have yet to develop
the sound cone!

16:33.410 --> 16:35.576
- Okay,
time to fight to the death.

16:35.662 --> 16:37.787
And don't do the thing
where you're friends,

16:37.831 --> 16:39.122
So you're conflicted
about fighting.

16:39.165 --> 16:40.748
Just really go at each other.

16:40.792 --> 16:41.749
Now!

16:41.835 --> 16:42.834
[both grunting softly]

16:42.919 --> 16:44.210
You're doing the exact thing

16:44.295 --> 16:45.712
I asked you not to do!

16:45.797 --> 16:46.713
Fight for real!

16:46.798 --> 16:49.090
[both grunting]

16:49.134 --> 16:51.300
- Ready!
[wolves growling]

16:51.386 --> 16:53.052
- Mutilate the wolves!
- Stop!

16:53.138 --> 16:55.013
We can be friends!

16:55.098 --> 16:57.223
This wolf and I slept together.

16:57.308 --> 16:59.684
[all chuckle]
oh, grow up!

16:59.769 --> 17:01.227
- That's sweet, sis,

17:01.271 --> 17:03.438
But I don't think
these wolves understand.

17:03.565 --> 17:06.232
- Wolf, you can understand me,
right?

17:06.317 --> 17:07.442
- [barks]

17:07.527 --> 17:09.944
- Okay, great.
I'll talk to my army,

17:09.988 --> 17:11.571
And you translate for yours.

17:11.656 --> 17:12.655
Listen to me!

17:12.866 --> 17:15.616
Humans and wolves
are not that different!

17:15.702 --> 17:17.785
- [barking]

17:17.829 --> 17:19.746
- We're smart but violent.

17:19.831 --> 17:21.998
- [barking]

17:22.083 --> 17:24.333
- We're especially mean
to our own kind.

17:24.377 --> 17:26.502
- [barking]

17:26.546 --> 17:29.756
- Maybe we finally found
the one animal

17:29.841 --> 17:31.382
That really gets us.

17:31.426 --> 17:34.510
- [barking]

17:37.098 --> 17:39.515
<i> [inspiring music]</i>

17:39.601 --> 17:42.810
[all howl]

17:42.896 --> 17:44.353
[all murmuring]

17:44.397 --> 17:46.314
- We're gonna be friends
with wolves.

17:46.399 --> 17:49.484
- [barking]

17:51.362 --> 17:53.654
[both grunting]

17:53.740 --> 17:54.697
- Hiya!

17:54.741 --> 17:55.698
- [shudders]

17:55.742 --> 17:56.949
[both grunting]

17:56.993 --> 17:58.284
- Stop!

17:58.369 --> 18:00.870
We won't fight anymore,
and here's why.

18:00.955 --> 18:02.080
We have something
you don't hav--

18:02.165 --> 18:03.122
- [grunts]
- [groans]

18:03.166 --> 18:05.083
[weakly] integrity.

18:05.168 --> 18:06.959
- Carrots!
- Are you satisfied?

18:07.087 --> 18:08.252
Have you seen enough blood?

18:08.296 --> 18:10.213
- No, I haven't seen any.

18:10.256 --> 18:12.131
I can't believe
you guys tried to pull

18:12.175 --> 18:14.175
The fake telescoping
spear trick.

18:14.302 --> 18:15.885
- Okay, okay,
you caught us there.

18:15.970 --> 18:17.720
- You do understand now
I have to kill you both?

18:17.847 --> 18:19.472
- Of course,
it makes a lot of sense

18:19.557 --> 18:21.015
That this would offend you,
and you know why?

18:21.059 --> 18:25.394
Because the lesson is,
nobody likes to be manipulated.

18:26.231 --> 18:27.522
He gets it!
He's nodding.

18:27.607 --> 18:29.690
- No, no,
I was imagining a kickass song

18:29.734 --> 18:30.691
To murder you by.

18:30.735 --> 18:32.902
♪ dun, dun, dun, dun, die! ♪

18:32.987 --> 18:35.029
♪ die, die, die, die, die! ♪

18:35.115 --> 18:35.947
- But I think if you think--

18:35.990 --> 18:36.989
Ah!

18:37.033 --> 18:38.407
- Whoa!

18:38.493 --> 18:41.410
<i> [dramatic music]</i>

18:41.496 --> 18:42.829
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

18:42.872 --> 18:44.205
Uh...

18:45.333 --> 18:48.292
[shuddering]

18:49.337 --> 18:50.586
Oh, my god!

18:51.673 --> 18:53.965
[retching]

18:54.008 --> 18:55.007
[moans]
- [clears throat]

18:55.093 --> 18:57.093
Let it out.
Let's go.

18:57.137 --> 18:58.219
- I hate you!

18:58.304 --> 19:00.138
- Yeah, yeah.
You comin' home?

19:00.181 --> 19:01.556
Or do you wanna
keep being free?

19:01.599 --> 19:03.933
- [mutters] I'll come home,
but I hate you.

19:04.018 --> 19:04.976
- Dolphins!

19:05.019 --> 19:06.394
Dolphins?

19:06.437 --> 19:07.812
See?
Called it.

19:07.897 --> 19:09.355
Already dead.
Whale!

19:09.440 --> 19:12.358
<i> [dramatic music]</i>

19:12.443 --> 19:18.489
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

19:18.533 --> 19:21.701
<i> [serene lute music]</i>

19:21.786 --> 19:22.743
- Light is dangerous.

19:22.829 --> 19:23.953
- All move as one.

19:23.997 --> 19:25.246
- Water is air.
- All right.

19:25.290 --> 19:27.373
You're human, and he's gone.

19:27.417 --> 19:29.292
- Did it work?
- Of course it worked!

19:29.377 --> 19:31.460
It's not like poseidon's
going to choose now

19:31.504 --> 19:32.587
To become unpredictable.

19:32.630 --> 19:33.963
- Can I just ask, mom,

19:34.048 --> 19:36.340
Whose dismembered human
and horse appendages those are?

19:36.426 --> 19:38.217
- Actually, you can't ask,
because the lesson here

19:38.261 --> 19:40.219
Is never question my judgment.

19:40.305 --> 19:42.430
- I'm good with that lesson.
- I'm carrots.

19:42.557 --> 19:45.433
- No new friends, carrots,
and find your own way home.

19:45.476 --> 19:47.101
- You're a good guy,
carrots the centaur,

19:47.187 --> 19:48.853
And a good horse, combined.

19:48.897 --> 19:52.190
- We haven't seen the last
of each other, king tyrannis.

19:52.275 --> 19:53.191
Yah!

19:53.276 --> 19:54.525
[pants]

19:54.611 --> 19:56.485
- He says "yah" to himself?

19:56.529 --> 19:58.529
- Haven't seen the last
of each other?

19:58.573 --> 20:01.449
Like he gets to decide
how enduring a character he is.

20:01.492 --> 20:02.617
[tuts]
both: Centaurs.

20:02.660 --> 20:04.619
- Mom, you were right.
I can't keep being

20:04.704 --> 20:08.122
So critical of you if I'm just
as much of a spoiled assface.

20:08.208 --> 20:09.999
- Yes, yes, it's possible

20:10.043 --> 20:11.209
It was unfair of me
to trick you.

20:11.294 --> 20:13.118
Right, what animal
do you want to go home on?

20:13.171 --> 20:14.712
- An eagle!
- You don't get to choose.

20:14.797 --> 20:16.464
Tricked you!
Whale!

20:17.884 --> 20:19.091
- Inspired choice.

20:19.135 --> 20:21.969
- He didn't invent
summoning whales.

20:22.055 --> 20:24.013
- Mom, mom, mom--mom!
Mom!

20:24.057 --> 20:26.349
[gargling]
mom!

20:31.022 --> 20:33.564
[wolves barking]
- how's it going?

20:33.650 --> 20:36.275
- Well, they are interested
in a domestic relationship.

20:36.361 --> 20:38.319
- That's great.
- I don't know.

20:38.404 --> 20:40.321
They want to live in our houses

20:40.406 --> 20:41.989
And sleep in our beds
and eat our food.

20:42.033 --> 20:43.616
They want to be
escorted outside

20:43.701 --> 20:46.369
So they can poop and pee
wherever they want,

20:46.412 --> 20:47.536
And whenever they do it,

20:47.580 --> 20:49.413
They want to be told
they're good at it.

20:49.499 --> 20:52.416
- Okay, that took a turn.
What are they offering us?

20:52.502 --> 20:54.001
Can we milk them?

20:54.045 --> 20:56.379
- No!
No milking, no hauling.

20:56.422 --> 20:59.298
Look, I'm a very
interspecies kind of guy,

20:59.384 --> 21:02.927
But this is the most one-sided
proposal I've ever heard,

21:03.012 --> 21:06.055
And I can't advise mankind
to do anything else

21:06.099 --> 21:08.099
But walk the hell away.

21:08.184 --> 21:09.809
- You guys,
look at their offspring.

21:09.894 --> 21:12.728
It's like their puppies are
intentionally becoming cuter.

21:12.772 --> 21:14.855
- But the negotiations
aren't really--

21:14.899 --> 21:17.233
Okay, look at this lil' guy.

21:17.360 --> 21:19.652
[baby talk] are you a lil' guy?
Yes, you are.

21:19.696 --> 21:21.988
[normal voice] just go in there
and agree to everything.

21:22.031 --> 21:23.656
Stop being a jerk.

21:23.700 --> 21:24.573
- [sighs]

21:24.659 --> 21:25.783
<i> [suspenseful music]</i>

21:25.868 --> 21:28.995
- [growling]

21:29.872 --> 21:31.414
<i> - Did you get any of that?</i>

21:33.710 --> 21:35.459
<i> - Bento.</i>
<i> [all cheering]</i>
